Craft Face-Swap Video Lures with DeepFaceLab
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Install and configure DeepFaceLab on Linux for deepfake video creation
Extract and process facial data from source and target videos
Train a deepfake model to perform realistic face swaps
Generate convincing face-swap videos for social engineering awareness
Understand the technical process behind deepfake creation and detection
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line knowledge
Understanding of video file formats (MP4, AVI)
Familiarity with machine learning concepts
Warning: This lab is for educational and awareness purposes only. Creating deepfakes without consent is illegal and unethical.
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides a Linux-based cloud machine for this lab. Click Start Lab to access your dedicated environment. The machine comes with a bare metal Linux installation, so you'll install all required tools during the lab.

Task 1: Set up DeepFaceLab for Video Manipulation
Subtask 1.1: Install System Dependencies
Update the system and install required packages:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip git wget unzip ffmpeg cmake build-essential
sudo apt install -y python3-opencv libopencv-dev python3-tk
Subtask 1.2: Install CUDA Support (Optional but Recommended)
Check for GPU availability:

lspci | grep -i nvidia
If NVIDIA GPU is available, install CUDA toolkit:

wget https://developer.download.nvidia.com/compute/cuda/repos/ubuntu2004/x86_64/cuda-ubuntu2004.pin
sudo mv cuda-ubuntu2004.pin /etc/apt/preferences.d/cuda-repository-pin-600
wget https://developer.download.nvidia.com/compute/cuda/12.0.0/local_installers/cuda-repo-ubuntu2004-12-0-local_12.0.0-525.60.13-1_amd64.deb
sudo dpkg -i cuda-repo-ubuntu2004-12-0-local_12.0.0-525.60.13-1_amd64.deb
sudo cp /var/cuda-repo-ubuntu2004-12-0-local/cuda-*-keyring.gpg /usr/share/keyrings/
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y cuda
Subtask 1.3: Download and Setup DeepFaceLab
Clone the DeepFaceLab repository:

cd /home/ubuntu
git clone https://github.com/iperov/DeepFaceLab.git
cd DeepFaceLab
Install Python dependencies:

pip3 install -r requirements-cuda.txt
# If no CUDA, use: pip3 install -r requirements.txt
Subtask 1.4: Prepare Sample Videos
Create workspace directory and download sample videos:

mkdir -p workspace/data_src workspace/data_dst
cd workspace

# Download sample videos (replace with your own videos)
wget -O data_src.mp4 "https://sample-videos.com/zip/10/mp4/SampleVideo_1280x720_1mb.mp4"
wget -O data_dst.mp4 "https://sample-videos.com/zip/10/mp4/SampleVideo_1280x720_2mb.mp4"
Task 2: Create Face-Swap Videos
Subtask 2.1: Extract Frames from Source Video
Extract frames from the source video (person whose face will be swapped):

cd /home/ubuntu/DeepFaceLab
python3 main.py extract --input-dir workspace --output-dir workspace/data_src --detector s3fd --debug-dir workspace/data_src/debug
Subtask 2.2: Extract Frames from Destination Video
Extract frames from the destination video (target video where face will be replaced):

python3 main.py extract --input-dir workspace --output-dir workspace/data_dst --detector s3fd --debug-dir workspace/data_dst/debug
Subtask 2.3: Extract Faces from Source Images
Extract and align faces from source frames:

python3 main.py extract --input-dir workspace/data_src --output-dir workspace/data_src/aligned --detector s3fd --debug-dir workspace/data_src/aligned/debug
Subtask 2.4: Extract Faces from Destination Images
Extract and align faces from destination frames:

python3 main.py extract --input-dir workspace/data_dst --output-dir workspace/data_dst/aligned --detector s3fd --debug-dir workspace/data_dst/aligned/debug
Subtask 2.5: Train the Deepfake Model
Start training the face-swap model:

python3 main.py train --training-data-src-dir workspace/data_src/aligned --training-data-dst-dir workspace/data_dst/aligned --model-dir workspace/model --model SAEHD
Note: Training can take several hours. For demonstration purposes, you can stop after 1000-2000 iterations by pressing 'q' and Enter.

Subtask 2.6: Convert and Merge Faces
Convert the destination video with the trained model:

python3 main.py convert --input-dir workspace/data_dst --output-dir workspace/data_dst/merged --aligned-dir workspace/data_dst/aligned --model-dir workspace/model --model SAEHD
Subtask 2.7: Create Final Video
Merge the converted frames back into a video:

python3 main.py videoed merge-mp4 --input-dir workspace/data_dst/merged --output-file workspace/result.mp4 --reference-file workspace/data_dst.mp4
